{"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TimeZoneRef","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is refcounted and immutable."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each time zone has an identifier (for example, ‘Europe\/London’) which is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platform dependent. See [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.TimeZone.new"},{"text":"] for information on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identifier formats. The identifier of a time zone can be retrieved using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.get_identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A time zone contains a number of intervals. Each interval has an abbreviation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to describe it (for example, ‘PDT’), an offset to UTC and a flag indicating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if the daylight savings time is in effect during that interval. A time zone","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always has at least one interval — interval 0. Note that interval abbreviations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are not the same as time zone identifiers (apart from ‘UTC’), and cannot be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed to [ctor"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every UTC time is contained within exactly one interval, but a given"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"local time may be contained within zero, one or two intervals (due to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"incontinuities associated with daylight savings time).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An interval may refer to a specific period of time (eg: the duration"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of daylight savings time during 2010) or it may refer to many periods","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of time that share the same properties (eg: all periods of daylight","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"savings time).  It is also possible (usually for political reasons)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that some properties (like the abbreviation) change between intervals"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without other properties changing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneref"]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(_:)-3wi4a","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(_:)-5j2y","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(_:)-7gvn1","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(_:)-8j5ou","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(_:)-8m404","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(identifier:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(identifierOrUtc:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(offset:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","generated":true},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/ptr"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/doc